author: Meagan Damore
title: Screen Junkies Put on Their Nostalgia Glasses for ‘Jurassic World’ Honest Trailer
text:
Screen Junkies Put on Their Nostalgia Glasses for ‘Jurassic World’ Honest Trailer Tuesday, October 13th, 2015 at 4:59pm PST Tweet 
Chris Pratt won’t shut up about animals, Bryce Dallas Howard really likes assets and Vincent D’Onofrio has a Dr. Evil-level plan in the “Jurassic World” Honest Trailer. The Screen Junkies poke fun at the latest nostalgia-filled installment in the “Jurassic Park” franchise, admitting that — yeah, okay — the last final fight between the velociraptor, T-Rex and Indominous Rex was pretty cool. 
Chris Pratt and Bryce Dallas Howard are both scheduled to return in 2018 for the next installment, with Colin Trevorrow and Derek Connolly writing the script. Trevorrow is not expected to direct, and will instead serve as an executive producer alongside Steven Spielberg, who directed the first two entries in the “Jurassic Park” franchise.
